title: Card spending change
caption: Comparison between 2019 (baseline) and subsequent years' daily consumer debit and credit card spending within 1 February, 2020 and 2 May, 2021 in Austin, TX.
insights: Between mid-March and beginning of April, 2020 there was a mean decline of -45% in card spending across transportation, warehousing, health care, social assistance, general merchandise stores , arts, entertainment, recreation, accomodation and food service sectors compared to 2019.
In contrast, spending in the grocery and foodstore increased by 40% for the same period and has remained greater than 2019 observations.
Card spending began to rise towards the baseline after the beginning of April, 2020 but has remained about -9% below 2019 observations on average since August, 2020.
